originalText.text: I think this place is under new management now, last guys got in some legal trouble and I think it goes by the name of Outcome now. Either way, the training rooms are pretty drab, but I guess they do the job. Good fax machine in the business center, capable of handling big jobs quickly. Overall, a solid training program and I came out feeling like a whole new person. Can't do five stars because I wish it were a little closer to the East River.

originalText.text:
Good training programme on the whole with mostly positives and some negatives.

On the positive I seem to be immune to the effects of car crashes (and I’ve had a few! Mostly in tunnels bizarrely!!) Although the other guys didn’t do so well.  I’ve also got quite good at hand to hand combat with inadequate makeshift weapons.  I beat a guy who attacked me with a blade and a machine  gun in Paris I had a Bic biro pen!… German chap had a tussle with me with a kitchen knife and I put him to the sword with a rolled up copy of the gay times. Chap in tangiers kicked off with a pistol and a cut throat razor. Nailed him with a soft flannel (like Monty python’s Spanish Inquisition…)

On the negative side, My love life hasn’t been the best as I’ve got through 2 girlfriends.  Decor a bit bland too. The hot tub hasn’t worked properly for years.

Oh and there’s a cracking fax machine downstairs, takes fully bound documents and doesn’t jam.  Bargain.

originalText.text: I’ve been training here since I was bourne. I never get injured in a car accident. I always have to keep my hair dyed black and short for a reason they didn’t say or I just can’t remember. Fish tank had no fish but great for cold bath therapy. Volunteer program throws in a free tag necklace.

originalText.text: Great training program, but you can't choose your own identity name.  I was hoping for JSON Boering. Has a bit of tech and German flair to it. Food was lousy but the air conditioning was good. I was able to move my arms and hands impossibly fast during fights and it made a swishing sound when I swung them. Would recommend.
